          <li><strong class="text-text-primary">Business calculators</strong> (profit margin, overhead, labor rate, etc.) provide general guidance. Consult an accountant or financial advisor for decisions affecting your business finances.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-text-primary">Templates</strong> (invoices, estimates, service agreements, etc.) are starting points. Have a qualified attorney review any legal documents, contracts, or agreements before use.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-text-primary">Cost estimators</strong> produce ballpark ranges based on national averages and general multipliers. Actual costs vary by region, market conditions, material availability, and job-specific factors.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
